issues.body:
While I was implementing the transaction feature I notices a curious behaviour that happened in the unittests 

a getter threw an exception that a defined property does not exist. I found my bug but I was curious. I tested if this is a behaviour that can be easily reproduced.

php 7.2 + zephir 1.0.7

2 classes:

TestCase: 
```zephir
namespace Bugreport;

class PropertyIsGoingToDisappear {
    protected _magicProperty;

    public function setProperty(param) {
        let this->_magicProperty = param;

        return this;
    }

    public function getProperty() {
        return this->_magicProperty;
    }
}
```
and
```zephir
namespace Bugreport;

class MyClass {

    protected _property1;

    public function useSetterOfChild() {
        var myValue, instanceToBeReturned;

        let instanceToBeReturned = new PropertyIsGoingToDisappear();
        return instanceToBeReturned->setProperty(myValue);
    }
}

```
invoked by 
```php
$myObject = new Bugreport\MyClass();
$returnedObject = $myObject->useSetterOfChild();

// same as the returned object
$myOtherObject = new Bugreport\PropertyIsGoingToDisappear();
$myOtherObject->setProperty(1);

var_dump($myOtherObject->getProperty());
var_dump($returnedObject->getProperty());
```

results in 
```sh
/home/j/development/repos/bugreport-zephir/test.php:19:
int(1)
PHP Notice:  Undefined property: Bugreport\PropertyIsGoingToDisappear::$_magicProperty in /home/j/development/repos/bugreport-zephir/test.php on line 20
PHP Stack trace:
PHP   1. {main}() /home/j/development/repos/bugreport-zephir/test.php:0
PHP   2. Bugreport\PropertyIsGoingToDisappear->getProperty() /home/j/development/repos/bugreport-zephir/test.php:20
/home/j/development/repos/bugreport-zephir/test.php:20:
NULL
```

the issue is 
```zephir
var myValue, instanceToBeReturned;
instanceToBeReturned->setProperty(myValue);
```

the var has no value assigned so instead of setting a null value it removes the property in runtime, which is a quite curious sideeffect.

Here is the config.json
```js
{
    "namespace": "utils",
    "name": "utils",
    "description": "An utils helper extension",
    "author": "aiddroid",
    "version": "0.0.1",
    "verbose": false,
    "requires": {
        "extensions": []
    },
    "globals": {
        "utils.enable_cache": {
            "type": "bool",
            "default": true
        }
    }
}
```
but got "utils.utils.enable_cache" in phpinfo().
<img width="978" alt="phpinfo" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3241146/32821231-f2d9b916-c997-11e7-808b-f36ea378c770.png">

and after I removed the "utils" prefix from globals section in config.json, The key became "enable_cache" in phpinfo().It's very strange.
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3241146/32821339-678449b6-c998-11e7-96d3-313b3cbb41e4.png)

When extending zephir class which has static field it's changing it's value from `NULL` to `&NULL` in php 7 and 7.1, for php 5.5 and 5.6 it works fine.

Related PR with test - https://github.com/phalcon/zephir/pull/1535

@sjinks

When ajax request more than 3 times, there will be "Access to undeclared static property"
E.g
```zep
namespace XqKeji;

class Di
{
	private static _default;

	public static function getInstance()
	{
		var di
		let di = self::_default;

		if !di {
			let di = new self();
			let self::_default = di;
		}

		return self::_default;
	}
}
```

```zep
class app
{
	public function __construct()
	{
		var di;
		let di = \XqKeji\Di::getInstance();
	}
}
```
Test:

```php
<?php
$App = new App();

```
 in window php7.0 ts

`StaticProperty::assignStatic`:

```php
if ($compilationContext->insideCycle) {
    $propertyCache = $compilationContext->symbolTable->getTempVariableForWrite('zend_property_info', $compilationContext);
    $propertyCache->setMustInitNull(true);
    $propertyCache->setReusable(false);
    $codePrinter->output('zephir_update_static_property_ce_cache(' . $classEntry .', SL("' . $property . '"), &' . $tempVariable->getName() . ', &' . $propertyCache->getName() . ' TSRMLS_CC);');
} else {
     $compilationContext->backend->updateStaticProperty($classEntry, $property, $tempVariable, $compilationContext);
}
```

However, `zephir_update_static_property_ce_cache` is available only in ZE2 kernel.

https://github.com/phalcon/zephir/blob/master/Library/Statements/Let/StaticProperty.php#L208
https://github.com/phalcon/zephir/blob/master/Library/Statements/Let/StaticProperty.php#L224

```c
PHP_METHOD(Test_SPropertyAccess, __construct) {

	zval *_0, _1, _2, *_3, *_4 = NULL;

	ZEPHIR_MM_GROW();

	ZEPHIR_INIT_ZVAL_NREF(_0);
	ZEPHIR_INIT_VAR(_0);
	ZVAL_STRING(_0, "abc", 1);
```

Both `ZEPHIR_INIT_ZVAL_NREF` and `ZEPHIR_INIT_VAR` allocate memory via `ALLOC_ZVAL`; memory allocated by `ZEPHIR_INIT_ZVAL_NREF` is leaked.

```c
zval _2$$3 = zval_used_for_init;

	while (1) {
		if (!(i < zephir_fast_strlen_ev(value))) {
			break;
		}
		_1$$3 = ZEPHIR_STRING_OFFSET(value, i);
		ZEPHIR_SINIT_NVAR(_2$$3);
		ZVAL_STRINGL(&_2$$3, &_1$$3, 1, 1);
		ZEPHIR_CALL_FUNCTION(&_3$$3, "ord", &_4, 79, &_2$$3);
		zephir_check_call_status();
		ZEPHIR_CALL_FUNCTION(&_5$$3, "dechex", &_6, 6, _3$$3);
		zephir_check_call_status();
		zephir_concat_self(&ret, _5$$3 TSRMLS_CC);
		i++;
	}
	RETURN_CTOR(ret);
```

As a result, the very last value of `_2$$3` will leak.

See: `Variable::initVariant()` in the compiler

PHP 5.6, `zim_Test_BuiltIn_CharMethods_getHexForString`

```
PHP_METHOD(Test_BuiltIn_CharMethods, getHexForString) {

	long _0;
	char ch = 0;
	zval *str_param = NULL, *o = NULL, *_1$$3 = NULL, *_2$$3 = NULL, _3$$3 = zval_used_for_init;
	zval *str = NULL;

	ZEPHIR_MM_GROW();
	zephir_fetch_params(1, 1, 0, &str_param);

	zephir_get_strval(str, str_param);


	ZEPHIR_INIT_VAR(o);
	ZVAL_STRING(o, "", 1);
	for (_0 = 0; _0 < Z_STRLEN_P(str); _0++) {
		ch = ZEPHIR_STRING_OFFSET(str, _0);
		ZEPHIR_INIT_NVAR(_2$$3);
		ZEPHIR_SINIT_NVAR(_3$$3);
		ZVAL_STRINGL(&_3$$3, &ch, 1, 1);
		zephir_string_to_hex(_2$$3, &_3$$3);
		zephir_concat_self(&o, _2$$3 TSRMLS_CC);
	}
	RETURN_CCTOR(o);

}
```

Interesting parts:
```c
zval _3$$3 = zval_used_for_init

for (_0 = 0; _0 < Z_STRLEN_P(str); _0++) {
	ZEPHIR_SINIT_NVAR(_3$$3);
	ZVAL_STRINGL(&_3$$3, &ch, 1, 1);
}
```

`ZEPHIR_SINIT_NVAR(z)` expands to `Z_SET_REFCOUNT_P(&z, 1)`

`ZVAL_STRINGL` in the loop overwrites the previous string which is never freed.

because PHP and zephir return different answers?

``` zephir
.zep

