review_comments.body:
The current implementation is much like a hack :-(

There is no `cleanup()` method or something like this, therefore we have to (ab)use `onPostCompile()`. But the issue is that in `postCompile()` the entire method has already been generated, and we have to deal with the code in the text form.

The current logic is as follows:
* we get the list of all used variables and filter only the local ones;
* for every local variable we add a call to `zval_dtor()`;
* all these calls are saved into a string;
* then we get the text code from the code printer and insert out string with `zval_dtor()`s right before the `RETURN_xxx` statement.

I know that this is not an elegant solution, but with the current implementation of the compiler I was unable to come up with something more beautiful :-(

